results.name: Smallest k such that A098550(n) + A098550(n+1) + ... + A098550(n+k) is prime, or -1 if there is no such k.
comment: In contrast to this conjecture, for the sequence of the positive integers (A=A000027) there are infinitely many n for which A(n) + A(n+1) + ... + A(n+k) is composite for every k>=0 (cf. A089306, A077654).
link: Peter J. C. Moses, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
